text: What us true regarding autonomous cars?

answer_options.answer_text: At no point in the FSA 2022 competition will it be required or an advantage to have an autonomous car or autonomous system components mounted in the car
The autonomous system can be presented in Engineering Design in order to gain extra points but can be removed for the Acceleration Event
Autonomous systems must not be activated in any dynamic displine, but they can be tested at a dedicated practice area on the competition site
Autonomous system components may stay in the car but at scrutineering it will not be checked that they are fully disabled by putting the ASMS in the "Off" position

text:
On your vehicles CAN network, two nodes have a message with the same ID queued:
 - Node A: ID 0x123, DLC 4, Date 0x55 0x55 0x55
 - Node B: ID 0x123, DLC 2, Date 0x00 0x00
 Both nodes start transmitting at the same time, which message will reach node C, which is setup to receive any 0x123 message, first if there is only a single attempt to transmit?

answer_options.answer_text: Node A, because Data Byte 0 has the higher value
Node B, because Data Byte o has the lower value
Node B, because the DLC has the lower value
neither, this will cause a collision on the bus

Node B, because Data Byte o has the lower value
Node B, because the DLC has the lower value
